ARTICLE 20 MISCELLANEOUS
20.1 Disclosure Exceptions: Each party reserves the right to disclose any terms of this Agreement to third parties without prior consent, provided that such disclosure is:

(i) Compliant with securities or other applicable laws;
(ii) Made to regulatory bodies, governmental authorities, or other entities as required by law;
(iii) Shared with prospective and other investors, but only upon execution of a nondisclosure agreement;
(iv) Communicated to the party's accountants, attorneys, and professional advisors on a need-to-know basis; or
(v) Divulged under circumstances where protection against unauthorized use or disclosure is assured.
